	<div class="commentTop">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a name="9468766">Re:This is what a rocket ship SHOULD look like....</a></h4>


		 	<span id="comment_score_9468766" class="score">(Score:3, Interesting)</span>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			by <a href="//slashdot.org/~Moofie">Moofie (22272)</a> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_9468766">		 &lt;<a href="mailto:lee+AT+ringofsaturn+DOT+com">lee AT ringofsaturn DOT com</a>&gt;
		on Friday June 18, @07:47PM (<a href="//slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=111496&amp;cid=9468766">#9468766</a>)
		<small><br>(<a href="http://moofie.lastcoolnameleft.com/">http://moofie.lastcoolnameleft.com/</a>) </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">	
		<div id="comment_body_9468766">Thanks for your reply.  This is something I've been really curious about since first reading about your design.<br> <br>My intuition was wrong:  I'm stunned that so little propellant is used for landing.  Nevertheless, you still need lots of propellant to schlep around your landing propellant through the boost phase.  About how much "extra" propellant would you estimate is required?  By my back-of-the-envelope thinking, it'd be about 800 lbs.<br> <br>Does your site have specs on the big vehicle's fuel consumption and thrust estimates?  I'd like to play around with your numbers.  Just to keep my hand in, you know...<br> <br>Impressive work.  I can't wait to see more.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_9468766">
[ <a href="//slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=111496&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;cid=9468631">Parent</a>
